1007. To LEo X. Farrago p. 354. [Louvain] F. p. 452: HN: Lond. xi. 9: LB. 453. 13 August 1519. [A further appeal to Papal authority against his opponents among the Louvain theologians, with whom he had not yet come to a reconciliation (cf. Ep. 1016. 1511). For prosecution of the appeal in other directions see Epp. 1033, 1060, 1062. The

date of time is confirmed by the Imperial Election (1. 106) ; but in view of the conflict with Ep. 1008 the place is perhaps only a permanent address (cf. p. 12).]
